column8: Wyoming Hunter and Angler's Gubernatorial Candidate Forum
column9:
Wyoming Wildlife Federation Presents:
The Hunter and Angler's Gubernatorial Candidate Forum

Lately we haven't been hearing much from the candidates on the issues that matter to hunters and anglers. So we wanted to make sure the hunters, anglers, and conservationists of Wyoming got the answers they are looking for. This forum is built to specifically highlight the issues we hold dear - including access, opportunity, healthy wildlife and fish populations, intact ecosystems, and clean air and water - with an aim of encouraging conversation and ultimately political action. 

You will hear questions concerning public lands, wildlife funding, sage grouse, wildlife migrations, and others. There will be space for a few screened questions from the audience at the end. 

The event will be held at Durham Hall Auditorium on the campus of Casper College, 6pm-9pm Thursday, August 9th. Casper Wyoming

Press will be present. Event will be recorded and we will be streaming live on Facebook. 

A casual after party will follow for those attending the event. Location TBD.

barn‚Ä¢storm (Ààb…ërnÀåst…îrm) 
 v.i.
 1. to conduct a campaign in rural areas by making brief stops in many small towns.

 Democrats can win in November, but only if we can get people excited and mobilized. Join us and your neighbors who want to change the way the state is moving, who believe that Democrats care about people and can think for ourselves, and who want to make the world a better place. column8: Honoring the Voting Rights Act with Dr. Josie Johnson
column9:
Come honor the 53rd anniversary of the Voting Rights Act with Dr. Josie Johnson, State Senator Bobby Joe Champion, U.S. Senator Tina Smith, and a first-time voter. In recognizing the importance of this historic legislation, we'll hear from some of the Minnesota leaders who have first-hand experience in extending voting rights. While this is a celebration of the progress that has been made, it is also a recognition of the work that still needs to be done.
 
 After the remarks, you are invited to join Senator Smith in casting your vote in the Minnesota Primary Election. A reminder that if you plan to vote, no specific candidate apparel (including shirts, buttons, and signs) may be visible when voting. While you may wear political attire, no candidate attire is allowed if the candidate is on the ballot.
 
 RSVP here: https://secure.ngpvan.com/7vxJLFWHb0inyFgg_k1OyQ2
 
 Check that you're registered to vote here: https://mnvotes.sos.state.mn.us/VoterStatus.aspx

column8: Lake of the Woods Unity Reception for Abigail Spanberger
column9:
Please join the Tri-County Democrats (Spotsylvania, Culpeper, and Orange County), Lake of the Woods Democratic Club, and master of ceremonies Dan Ward, former VA07 Democratic candidate, for a unity reception in support of Abigail Spanberger, the Democratic nominee for Congress in Virginia‚Äôs 7th District.
 
 **********************************
 DETAILS, RSVP, and LOCATION
 
 Join our Unity Team!
 ‚Ä¢ $20 Unity Supporter
 ‚Ä¢ $50 Unity Enthusiast
 ‚Ä¢ $100 Unity Fanatic
 
 Please RSVP to confirm your attendance:
 http://bit.ly/Aug11RSVP
 
 Lake of the Woods Community Center
 110 Sweetbriar Park Rd.
 Locust Grove, VA 22508
 
 **********************************
 Abigail began her career of public service as a federal law enforcement officer working narcotics and money laundering cases with the US Postal Inspection Service. Following her love of country, public service, and languages, Abigail joined the CIA as an Operations Officer. She traveled and lived abroad collecting intelligence, managing assets, and overseeing high-profile programs in service to the United States. In 2014, Abigail left government service to begin a career in the private sector and bring her and her family back home to Virginia. Working at EAB ‚Äì Royall & Company, Abigail has worked with colleges and universities to create diverse student bodies, increase graduation rates, and break down financial barriers to higher education.
 
 Abigail grew up in Short Pump, in Henrico County. She attended J.R. Tucker High School‚Äôs Spanish immersion program, served as a Senate Page for US Senator Chuck Robb (D-VA), and graduated from the University of Virginia. After college, Abigail moved to Germany and earned her MBA from a dual-degree German-American program between the GISMA business school and Purdue University.
 
 Abigail and her husband, Adam, live with their children in Glen Allen.
 
 Learn more about Abigail at www.abigailspanberger.com
